//https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=61K-2VRaC6s&list=PL4cUxeGkcC9h9RbDpG8ZModUzwy45tLjb

in terminal:
$ uv tool install specify-cli --from git+https://github.com/github/spec-kit.git@v0.12.1
$ specify init spec-kit-practice --integration copilot
$ cd spec-kit-practice 
$ specify version   

open a project in VScode, open terminal there (cmd+J)
$ uvx --from git+https://github.com/github/spec-kit.git specify init --here
then follow the prompts to finish applying spec-kit with copilot
by now there would be an extra folder called '.github' pulled to the project

/constitution -> /specify -> /plan -> /tasks -> /implement
/constitution doesnt need to be run every time as it is project-level governing principles.
optional commands would be /clarify which is following /specify, and /analyze which is following /tasks

how this workflow works:
input and run /constitution blablablabla~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
when we run /consitituion, it fires the constitution prompts, which tells the coding agent to fill in the constitution file in the memory folder by extracting any input we give it
and using that to fill in any placeholder tokens. 
